🔹 1. What is HashMap?
- HashMap ek data structure hai jo key-value pair me data store karta hai
- Har key unique hoti hai, value duplicate ho sakti hai
👉 Example:
map.put(1, "A");
map.put(2, "B");

🔹 2. Internal Working ?
- Internally HashMap hash table use karta hai,Hash table actually array of buckets hoti hai
- Har bucket me:
          LinkedList / Tree (Java 8 ke baad)
- initial table size = 16
- load factor / threshold = 0.75
👉 Flow: 
       key → hashCode() → index → bucket → value

🔹 3. Ordering Behavior ?
❌ Insertion order maintain nahi karta
❌ Sorting follow nahi karta
✔ Random order me data store hota hai

🔹 4. Time Complexity ?
| Operation                 | Complexity   |
| ------------------------- | ------------ |
| put() (new)               | O(1) avg     |
| get()                     | O(1) avg     |
| remove()                  | O(1) avg     |
| **update (existing key)** | **O(1) avg** |
👉 Worst case: O(n) (jab collision zyada ho).

🔹 5. Important Methods ?
✔ put() : 
       👉 Same key pe new value old value ko replace kar deti hai.
        ex -  map.put(2, "meraz");
              map.put(2, "sahil"); // overwrite karega

✔ get() :
       👉 Agar key exist nahi karti → null return karega.
        ex - map.get(5);

✔ containsKey() :
        👉 true / false return karega.
        ex - map.containsKey(5);

✔ getOrDefault() :
         👉 Agar key nahi mile → default value return hogi.
         ex - map.getOrDefault(5, "value not present");

✔ replace() :
         👉 Sirf tab update karega jab key exist karti ho.
          ex - map.replace(2, "alam");

✔ remove() :
          👉 map.remove(2);



🔹 6. Iteration Techniques ?

✔ 1. Direct Print :
            👉 internally toString() call hota hai.
             ex - 
                 System.out.println(map);

✔ 2. entrySet() (Best Way ⭐) :
             ex - 
                   for (Map.Entry<Integer, String> entry : map.entrySet()) {
                       System.out.println(entry.getKey());
                       System.out.println(entry.getValue());
                   }

✔ 3. keySet() :
            ex - 
                   for (Integer key : map.keySet()) {
                           System.out.println(key);
                           System.out.println(map.get(key));
                   }


🔹 7. Collision Handling ?
- Jab 2 keys ka hash same index pe aaye → collision
- Handle hota hai:
                 - LinkedList
                 - Tree (Java 8 ke baad, jab size > 8)


🔹 8. Important Note (Very Important for Interviews ⭐) ?
👉 Agar tum custom object ko key bana rahe ho:
✔ Must override:
               hashCode() : bucket decide karta hai.
               equals()  : exact key match check karta hai.




